comments: During the rebound, Kuzma (LAL) and Hachimura (WAS) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Bertans (WAS) is not established in a legal guarding position and moves laterally towards James (LAL) when marginal contact occurs.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball, but Morris (LAL) turns and delivers contact to Beal (WAS) during his drive to the basket.
Caruso (LAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Hachimura's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact as the defenders switch.
Hachimura (WAS) is in the paint and actively guarding an opponent within three seconds.
Avdija (WAS) brings his arms downward and they are not in a vertical position when he makes contact to James's (LAL) arm and the contact affects his driving shot attempt.
Bertans (WAS) places a forearm on Caruso's (LAL) back during the rebound and does not extend into him.  Caruso jumps towards the ball and his momentum carries him forward.
During the rebound, Caruso (LAL) reaches for the loose ball and incidental contact occurs with Westbrook's (WAS) arm on the follow-through after his back tap.
James (LAL) lifts and re-plants his pivot foot prior to the start of his dribble.
Kuzma (LAL) establishes himself in Hachimura's (WAS) path and places two resting hands on him without delivering contact or affecting Hachimura's ability to maintain his legal guarding position.
Hachimura (WAS) legally contests James' (LAL) jump shot attempt.
After the rebound, Caruso (LAL) brings two hands to the ball to cleanly tie it up with Avdija (WAS) and a jump ball is correctly whistled.

During the drive, Hachimura (WAS) extends his arm out and marginal contact occurs to James' (LAL) arm as he switches directions. James is able to play through the marginal contact and maintain his dribble.
Hachimura (WAS) places a resting hand on James' (LAL) shoulder and marginal contact occurs that does not affect James' play at the basket.
Morris (LAL) commits a take foul on Westbrook (WAS).
Westbrook (WAS) makes contact to James' (LAL) arm/body that affects his driving shot attempt.
During the rebound, Morris (LAL) and Lopez (WAS) are engaged and Morris makes incidental foot to foot contact with Hachimura (WAS) that causes him to lose his balance.
Beal (WAS) briefly fumbles the ball and only takes two steps upon gathering the ball prior to his jump shot attempt.
Hachimura (WAS) moves laterally into and makes contact with Caruso's (LAL) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) moves slightly into Beal (WAS) and marginal contact occurs that does not affect his SQBR at the end of his drive.
Kuzma (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Beal (WAS).
James (LAL) takes a step backwards with his pivot foot prior to the release of his dribble.
Hachimura (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact during the driving shot attempt by James (LAL).
Caruso (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Beal (WAS).
Hachimura (WAS) legally contests Caldwell-Pope's (LAL) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is deemed incidental.

Replay review of the foul called on Gasol (LAL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Gasol makes contact to Lopez (WAS) with his arm extended while Lopez is airborne during the pass.
James (LAL) makes contact with Westbrook's (WAS) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
During the rebound, Kuzma (LAL) and Mathews (WAS) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.

Westbrook (WAS) jumps to the side of Kuzma (LAL) to contest his jump shot attempt, and would have avoided contact if Kuzma did not extend is leg forward to initiate the marginal contact after the release.
